President Biden and King Abdullah II of Jordan had a discussion about regional and global issues. They talked about efforts to stop violence in Israel and the West Bank, particularly at the Haram al-Sharif/Temple Mount complex in Jerusalem. President Biden welcomed recent actions to reduce tensions and expressed his hope for a peaceful final week of Ramadan. He emphasized the importance of maintaining the historical status quo at the Haram al-Sharif/Temple Mount and recognized Jordan's role as the custodian of Muslim holy sites in Jerusalem. King Abdullah II informed the President about his recent engagements in the region, and President Biden reiterated the United States' commitment to the Middle East and regional stability.